moduleConfig.title: Applications started and submitted
info: Digital applications are counted as ‘started’ when the applicant creates an application for student finance. They are counted as ‘submitted’ when they complete and submit the application. This data includes automated applications counted as started and submitted on the same day, these are submitted on behalf of non means tested students expected to re-apply for student finance. Automated applications are created over a two week period in the early part of each new business cycle i.e. the academic year of intended study.

Any paper applications received are data entered into the system by SLC staff. Paper applications are counted as ‘started’ and ‘submitted’ when the processing team starts the data entry of the application.
